mod-rpaf-fork (0.7-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Build and run on both Apache 2.2 and Apache 2.4.
  * Use the real client IP behind a chain of proxies, validate and skip
    invalid X-Forwarded-For entries.
  * RPAFsetport applies the port per request instead of mutating server_rec.
  * RPAFsethttps no longer leaks the https scheme, sets the SSL flag used by
    RewriteCond %{HTTPS}, and validates the forwarded HTTPS header value.
  * RPAFsethostname uses the last entry of a comma-separated X-Forwarded-Host.

 -- Kentaro YOSHIDA <y.ken.studio@gmail.com>  Wed, 17 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0900
